hwWlanDevice.name: hwWlanDevice

revisions.description: Modify the range of hwApHighTemperatureThreshold and hwApLowTemperatureThreshold .
Modify the description of hwApForwardMode and add node hwApLocalAssocResSwitch.
Modify the nodes of hwWlanDeviceNotify and hwApRegionEntry.
Modify the name of hwEthportUpRate and hwEthportDownRate.The new name is hwApEthportUpRate and hwApEthportDownRate.
Modify the name of hwEthportUpRate and hwEthportDownRate.The new name is hwApEthportUpRate and hwApEthportDownRate.
Modify the name of hwEthportUpRate and hwEthportDownRate.The new name is hwApEthportUpRate and hwApEthportDownRate.
Add wids attack detection quiet-time parameter

V1.05, Add the ap-blacklist table for the supporting management of ap-blacklist, Add hwUnAuthorizedApRecordNumber and hwUnAuthorizedApRecordAdmin for supporting management of unauthorized-ap record, Modify the Max access read-only of hwApIpAddress to read-write, Delete the enum value wlan80211abgn(7) of the hwApTypeRadioType leaf.
V1.04, Add a leaf hwRadioMaxVAPNum in hwApTypeRadioTable

V1.03, Add an enum value unknown(-1) in hwApForwardMode leaf of hwApTable, Add an enum value unknown(-1) in hwApRegionForwardMode leaf of hwApRegionTable, Add an operation type replaceAp(6) in hwApAdminOper of hwApTable.
V1.01, Add hwApAntennaMode in hwApTable for the supporting configuration of ap antenna mode.

hwApFaultNotify.name: hwApFaultNotify
hwApFaultNotify.description: This notification occurs when AP become fault because of AP off line,reset or shutdown etc. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApSysName:AP name.

hwApNormalNotify.name: hwApNormalNotify
hwApNormalNotify.description: This notification occurs when AP become normal. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApSysName:AP name.

hwApTypeNotMatchNotify.name: hwApTypeNotMatchNotify
hwApTypeNotMatchNotify.description: This notification occurs when AP's actual type is not match the configured one. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApSysName:AP name, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApActualType: AP actual type.

hwApPingResultNotify.name: hwApPingResultNotify
hwApPingResultNotify.description: This notification occurs when AP has accomplished a ping and will report the result to user. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApSysName:AP name, hwApPingResultSuccessCount:the successful times of the recent AP ping, hwApPingResultFailureCount: the failed times of recent AP ping, hwApPingResultAverageResponseTime: the average response time of recent AP ping. hwApPingResultMinimumResponseTime: the minimum response time of recent AP ping. hwApPingResultMaximumResponseTime: the maximum response time of recent AP ping.

hwApColdstartNotify.name: hwApColdstartNotify
hwApColdstartNotify.description: This notification occurs when AP cold starting. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApSysName:AP name.

hwApConfigCommitNotify.name: hwApConfigCommitNotify
hwApConfigCommitNotify.description: This notification occurs when commit AP's configuration successfully. hwApIndex: AP ID.

hwApAddOffLineNotify.name: hwApAddOffLineNotify
hwApAddOffLineNotify.description: This notification occurs when add an AP off line. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApSysName:AP name, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApMac:AP MAC address, hwApSn:AP SN number.

hwApConfirmNotify.name: hwApConfirmNotify
hwApConfirmNotify.description: This notification occurs when confirm an AP successfully. hwApIndex: AP ID, hwApSysName:AP name, hwApUsedType: AP type, hwApUsedRegionIndex: AP region ID, hwApMac:AP MAC address, hwApSn:AP SN number.

hwApActualType.name: hwApActualType
hwApActualType.description: The actual type of AP. This node is used for describe the actual type of an AP tying to get online, which type can't be matched by AC.

hwApTypeTable.name: hwApTypeTable
hwApTypeTable.description: Huawei AP type table. The index of this table is hwApType. AP type is a string used to represent a kind of AP. AP type table include following attribute such as AP's type name, maximum station number, maximum SSID number, radio number and type, lineate port number and type etc.

hwApTypeEntry.name: hwApTypeEntry
hwApTypeEntry.description: Huawei AP type table entry.The index of this entry is hwApType. AP type is a string used to represent a kind of AP. AP type table include following attribute such as AP's type name, maximum statio nnumber, maximum SSID number, radio number and type, lineate port number and type etc.

hwApType.name: hwApType
hwApType.description: AP type is the identification of a kind of AP.

hwApTypeDesc.name: hwApTypeDesc
hwApTypeDesc.description: Description of AP type. The maximum string length is 63.

hwApTypeLineatePortNum.name: hwApTypeLineatePortNum
hwApTypeLineatePortNum.description: The lineate port number of AP.When add an AP type, its default lineateport number is 8.

hwApTypeRadioNum.name: hwApTypeRadioNum
hwApTypeRadioNum.description: The number of radios on the AP.When add an AP type, its default radios number is 4.

hwApTypeMaxStaNum.name: hwApTypeMaxStaNum
hwApTypeMaxStaNum.description: The maximum of station of AP.When add an AP type, its default access station number is 128.

hwApTypeMaxSsidNum.name: hwApTypeMaxSsidNum
hwApTypeMaxSsidNum.description: The maximum of ssid of AP.When add an AP type, its default max- imum SSID number is 32.

hwApTypeAntennaGain.name: hwApTypeAntennaGain
hwApTypeAntennaGain.description: The antenna gain of AP. Unit: dBi. Its default antenna gain is 0.

hwApTypeRowStatus.name: hwApTypeRowStatus
hwApTypeRowStatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP type addition and deletion.

hwApTypeRadioTable.name: hwApTypeRadioTable
hwApTypeRadioTable.description: Huawei AP type radio table. Each AP type has several radios, gene- rally 1 to 4 radios. The index of this table is hwApType in table hwApTypeTable and hwApTypeRadioIndex. It describes the following attributes of a radio inAP type, radio type, maximal spatial streams, maximal antenna number.

hwApTypeRadioEntry.name: hwApTypeRadioEntry
hwApTypeRadioEntry.description: Huawei AP type radio table entry.Each AP type has several radios, gene- rally 1 to 4 radios. The index of this entry is hwApType in table hwApTypeTable and hwApTypeRadioIndex. It describes the following attributes of a radio inAP type, radio type, maximal spatial streams, maximal antenna number.

hwApTypeRadioIndex.name: hwApTypeRadioIndex
hwApTypeRadioIndex.description: Index of radio in an AP type.

hwApTypeRadioType.name: hwApTypeRadioType
hwApTypeRadioType.description: The type of radio of AP type. When add an AP type ,the default radio type is wlan80211a(1).

hwRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum.name: hwRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum
hwRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum.description: Maximum spatial streams number of a radio in an AP type.When add an AP type ,its defautl value is 1 .

hwRadioMaxAntennasNum.name: hwRadioMaxAntennasNum
hwRadioMaxAntennasNum.description: Maximum antennas number of a radioin an AP type,defautl is 1 for no-80211n type radio, 0(Smart-Antennas-Array) for 80211n type radio.

hwRadioMaxVAPNum.name: hwRadioMaxVAPNum
hwRadioMaxVAPNum.description: Maximum VAP number of a radioin an AP type.

hwApTypeLineatePortInfoTable.name: hwApTypeLineatePortInfoTable
hwApTypeLineatePortInfoTable.description: Huawei AP type lineate port table.Each AP type may have several line- ate port.The index of this table is AP type in table hwApTypeTable and lineate port ID of AP type. The table describes the lineate port type of all AP type.

hwApTypeLineatePortInfoEntry.name: hwApTypeLineatePortInfoEntry
hwApTypeLineatePortInfoEntry.description: Huawei AP type lineate port table entry.Each AP type may have several lineate port.The index of this table is AP type in table hwApTypeTable and lineate port ID of AP type. The table describes the lineate port type of all AP type.

hwApTypeLineatePortIndex.name: hwApTypeLineatePortIndex
hwApTypeLineatePortIndex.description: Index of lineate port in an AP type.

hwApTypeLineatePortType.name: hwApTypeLineatePortType
hwApTypeLineatePortType.description: The type of lineate port of AP type.When add a new AP type, its default lineate port type is fe(1).

hwApProfileTable.name: hwApProfileTable
hwApProfileTable.description: Huawei AP profile table. The index of this tabel is AP profile name. AP profile is aggregate of a group of configuration. Such as, MTU of AP's Ethernet, DoS defend switch, working mode of AP, AP log backup server configuration, etc.

hwApProfileEntry.name: hwApProfileEntry
hwApProfileEntry.description: Huawei AP profile table entry.The index of this tabel is AP profile name. AP profile is aggregate of a group of configuration. Such as, MTU of AP's Ethernet, DoS defend switch, working mode of AP, AP log backup server configuration, etc.

hwApProfileName.name: hwApProfileName
hwApProfileName.description: Ap profile name identifies an AP profile, which include a set of AP's configuration.

hwApEthPortMtu.name: hwApEthPortMtu
hwApEthPortMtu.description: The maximal packet size of AP Ethernet.

hwApLogBackupServerIp.name: hwApLogBackupServerIp
hwApLogBackupServerIp.description: Ip address of AP's syslog backup server.

hwApProfileRowStatus.name: hwApProfileRowStatus
hwApProfileRowStatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP profile addition and deletion.

hwApMacWhitelistTable.description: Huawei AP mac address whitelist table. The Index of this table is mac address.AP mac address is used to authenticate the AP's validity.

hwApMacWhitelistEntry.name: hwApMacWhitelistEntry
hwApMacWhitelistEntry.description: Huawei AP mac address whitelist table entry. The Index of this table is mac address.AP mac address is used to authenticate the AP's validity.

hwApMacWhitelistRowStatus.name: hwApMacWhitelistRowStatus
hwApMacWhitelistRowStatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP mac whitelist addition and deletion.

hwApSnWhitelistTable.name: hwApSnWhitelistTable
hwApSnWhitelistTable.description: Huawei AP sn whitelist table. The index of this table is AP sn. AP sn is used to authenticate the AP's validity.

hwApSnWhitelistEntry.name: hwApSnWhitelistEntry
hwApSnWhitelistEntry.description: Huawei AP sn whitelist table entry.The index of this table is AP sn. AP sn is used to authenticate the AP's validity.

hwApAuthMode.name: hwApAuthMode
hwApAuthMode.description: Ap authentication mode. macAuth - AP is authenticated by mac-address. snAuth - AP is authenticated by sn. noAuth - no authentication. If select this mode, all AP will connect to the ac without authentication.

hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber.name: hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber
hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber.description: The start valid number of AP mac whitelist when get AP mac whitelist in batch. Begin with 0, must less than the specification of whitelist.

hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryNumber.name: hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryNumber
hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryNumber.description: The query number of AP mac whitelist when query AP mac whitelist in batch. The query number must less than or equal the specification of mac whitelist.

hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryList.name: hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryList
hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryList.description: The returned AP mac whitelist list when query AP mac whitelist in batch. The mac is storaged in the list one by one,and no separator. For example, if the start number is 10, and the query number is 50, then the host will find 50 valid mac whitelists from the 11th valid mac whitelist.(Assume there are 100 mac whitelists in host.) And each time the SNMP agent can get 128 mac whitelist at most.

hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber.name: hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber
hwApMacWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber.description: The actual mac number of returned AP mac whitelist list when query AP mac whitelist in batch.

hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber.name: hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber
hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryStartNumber.description: The start valid number of AP sn whitelist when get AP sn whitelist in batch. Begin with 0, must less than the specification of white- list.

hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryNumber.name: hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryNumber
hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryNumber.description: The query number of AP sn whitelist when query AP sn whitelist in batch. The query number must less than or equal the specification of whitelist.

hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryList.name: hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryList
hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryList.description: The returned AP sn whitelist list when query AP sn whitelist in batch. Two adjacent sn whitelist in the list are divided by '?'. For example, if the start number is 10, and the query number is 50, then the host will find 50 valid sn whitelists from the 11th valid sn whitelist.(Assume there are 100 sn whitelists in host.) And each time the SNMP agent can get 128 sn whitelist at most.

hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber.name: hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber
hwApSnWhitelistBatchQueryReturnNumber.description: The actual number of returned AP sn whitelist list when query AP sn whitelist in batch.

hwApMacBlacklistRowStatus.name: hwApMacBlacklistRowStatus
hwApMacBlacklistRowStatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP mac blacklist addition and deletion.

hwApRegionTable.name: hwApRegionTable
hwApRegionTable.description: Huawei AP region table. The index of this table is AP region ID. AP region is an aggregate of a lot of APs with the same position. Such as, all the APs in a building can be compartmentalized into one same region.

hwApRegionEntry.name: hwApRegionEntry
hwApRegionEntry.description: Huawei AP region table entry.The index of this table is AP region ID. AP region is an aggregate of a lot of APs with the same position. Such as, all the APs in a building can be compartmentalized into one same region.

hwApRegionName.name: hwApRegionName
hwApRegionName.description: The description of the AP region.

hwApRegionDeployMode.name: hwApRegionDeployMode
hwApRegionDeployMode.description: The AP's deploy mode in an AP region. discreteDeploy - all the APs in the region is deployed discretely. There is no disturbance between APs. Every AP works at the maximum power. normalDeploy - APs in the region is deployed sparsely. Ap works at 50% of the maximum power at least. discreteDeploy - APs in the region is deployed densely. Ap works at 25% of the maximum power at least.

hwApRegionApIndexMask.name: hwApRegionApIndexMask
hwApRegionApIndexMask.description: All APs's index mask in an AP region. Every bit is used to describe an AP is in this region or not. 0 means AP is not in this region, and 1 means AP is in this region.The value of this node is hexadecimal integer block. Each Byte describes 8 APs are in this region or not. For example, the first Byte describes AP 0~7 is in this region or not, and the second Byte describes AP 8~15 is in this region or not. Such as, if only AP 0,4,5,6,7,9 is in this region, the binary number is 11110001 and 00000010,the hexadecimal number is 0xF1 and 0x2, so the first Byte of this node is 0xF1,and the second Byte is 0x2.

hwApRegionRowStatus.name: hwApRegionRowStatus
hwApRegionRowStatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP region addition and deletion.

hwApRegionForwardMode.name: hwApRegionForwardMode
hwApRegionForwardMode.description: The Ap region based forward mode.

hwApRegionDefault.name: hwApRegionDefault
hwApRegionDefault.description: The default region index. When an AP connect to ac without addition, it will be added automatically, and join the default region.

hwApRegionAllExistRegionIndexMask.name: hwApRegionAllExistRegionIndexMask
hwApRegionAllExistRegionIndexMask.description: All the existent regions' index mask. Every bit is used to describe the region is existent or not. 0 means region is not existent, and 1 means region is existent. The value of this node is hexadecimal integer block. Each Byte describes 8 APs are existent or not. For example, the first Byte describes AP 0~7 is existent or not, and the second Byte describes AP 8~15 is existent or not. Such as, if only AP 0,4,5,6,7,9 is existent, the binary number is 11110001 and 00000010,the hexadecimal number is 0xF1 and 0x2, so the first Byte of this node is 0xF1,and the second Byte is 0x2.

hwApRegionBatchStart.name: hwApRegionBatchStart
hwApRegionBatchStart.description: The initiatory AP region number in batch operation. This node must be set in company with the node hwApRegionBatchNumber.

hwApRegionBatchNumber.name: hwApRegionBatchNumber
hwApRegionBatchNumber.description: The AP region number in batch operation. This node must be set in company with the node hwApRegionBatchStart.

hwApRegionBatchReturnNumber.name: hwApRegionBatchReturnNumber
hwApRegionBatchReturnNumber.description: The actual AP region number in batch operation.

hwApRegionBatchNameList.name: hwApRegionBatchNameList
hwApRegionBatchNameList.description: The actual AP region names in batch operation. Each profile name is divided by '?'.

hwApRegionBatchDeployMode.name: hwApRegionBatchDeployMode
hwApRegionBatchDeployMode.description: The deploy mode of AP regions in batch operation. The value of this node is hexadecimal integer block.Each region's deploy mode occupies a Byte. For example, if the first operated region's deploy mode is 15, and the sencond operated region's deploy mode is 14, so the first Byte of this node is 0xF,and the second Byte is 0xE.

hwApSrcRegionIndex.name: hwApSrcRegionIndex
hwApSrcRegionIndex.description: The source region index in a merge operation. When a merge operation has been done, all the APs in the source region will join the desti- nation region,and the source region will become a empty region.

hwApDestRegionIndex.name: hwApDestRegionIndex
hwApDestRegionIndex.description: The destination region index in a merge operation.

hwApTable.name: hwApTable
hwApTable.description: Huawei AP table. The index of this table is AP ID. The AP table des- cribes detailed information of all APs,including the AP's type, the run state of the AP, the software of the AP, the hardware version No., etc. When add an AP, AP type must be filled in. If current Ap authentication mode is MAC or SN, the MAC or SN of AP must be filled in. If current Ap authentication mode is noauth, one of the MAC or SN of AP must be filled in.

hwApEntry.name: hwApEntry
hwApEntry.description: Huawei AP table entry. The index of this table is AP ID. The AP table describes detailed information of all APs,including the AP's type, the run state of the AP, the software of the AP, the hardware version No.,etc. When add an AP, AP type must be filled in. If current Ap authentication mode is MAC or SN, the MAC or SN of AP must be filled in. If current Ap authentication mode is noauth, one of the MAC or SN of AP must be filled in.

hwApIndex.name: hwApIndex
hwApIndex.description: Ap index, is used to identify AP uniquely.

hwApUsedType.name: hwApUsedType
hwApUsedType.description: Ap type. For more details, please refer to hwApTypeTable.

hwApUsedProfileName.name: hwApUsedProfileName
hwApUsedProfileName.description: Ap profile name. For more details, please refer to hwApProfileTable.

hwApUsedRegionIndex.name: hwApUsedRegionIndex

hwApIpNetMask.name: hwApIpNetMask

hwApGatewayIp.name: hwApGatewayIp

hwApMemorySize.name: hwApMemorySize
hwApMemorySize.description: The memory size of AP. Unit: MB

hwApFlashSize.name: hwApFlashSize
hwApFlashSize.description: The flash size of AP. Unit: MB

hwApRunTime.name: hwApRunTime
hwApRunTime.description: The working time since AP is started.

hwApUpEthPortSpeedMode.name: hwApUpEthPortSpeedMode
hwApUpEthPortSpeedMode.description: The up ethernet port speed mode of AP.

hwApUpEthPortDuplex.name: hwApUpEthPortDuplex
hwApUpEthPortDuplex.description: The duplex type of the AP's up ethernet port. half(1) - half duplex, full(2) - full duplex.

hwApUpEthPortDuplexMode.name: hwApUpEthPortDuplexMode
hwApUpEthPortDuplexMode.description: The duplex mode of the AP's up ethernet port

hwApAdminOper.name: hwApAdminOper
hwApAdminOper.description: Ap administration operation. reset - reset the AP. confirm - when an AP which is not in the white list connects to ac, it will rest on join state. User can confirm it to make it to use. manufacturerConfig - reset AP to the manufacturing default config- uration

hwApRowstatus.name: hwApRowstatus
hwApRowstatus.description: Row status: mainly to support AP addition and deletion.

hwApRunningMode.name: hwApRunningMode
hwApRunningMode.description: Running mode of AP. auto - If AP connects an AC, it will run in fit mode, or it will run in fat mode. fat - Force AP to run in fat mode. fit - Force AP to run in fit mode.

hwApForwardMode.name: hwApForwardMode
hwApForwardMode.description: Set AP based forward mode. directForward(1) - direct forward mode, station data is direct forward. tunnel(2) - CAPWAP tunnel forward mode, station data is forward through the CAPWAP tunnel to ensure the security.

hwApAntennaMode.name: hwApAntennaMode
hwApAntennaMode.description: Ap antenna mode, used to select antenna mode,default is auto mode.

hwApAttackWeakivQuietTime.description: Weak-iv attack quiet time. Range from 60s to 36000s

hwApAttackSpoofQuietTime.name: hwApAttackSpoofQuietTime
hwApAttackSpoofQuietTime.description: Spoof attack quiet time. Range from 60s to 36000s

Every bit is used to describe the AP is existent or not.0 means AP is not existent, and 1 means AP is existent.The value of this node is hexadecimal integer block.Each Byte describes 8 APs are existent or not. For example, the first Byte describes AP 0~7 is existent or not, and the second Byte describes AP 8~15 is existent or not. Such as, if only AP 0,4,5,6,7,9 is existent, the binary number is 11110001 and 00000010,the hexadecimal number is 0xF1 and 0x2, so the first Byte of this node is 0xF1,and the second Byte is 0x2.

hwApBatchIndexReturnNumber.name: hwApBatchIndexReturnNumber
hwApBatchIndexReturnNumber.description: The actual AP number in batch operation.
